riggered the second you kill the next spawn.  Anyway, I've done a lot of work (several hours) to get a couple of the rare spawns to pop, and the minute I do, I wonder if that mob will be there when I get there.  I've arrived to the area which the next spawn pops only to see someone killing the mob I've worked so hard to spawn.  I've tried to keep my cool, but sometimes I admit I've lost it a few times (I regret my behavior now), but it is frustrating.  When I asked them what they were doing, they said they were just passing through and saw this named mob and decided to kill it (how convenient for them).  Sometimes I've gotten in shouting matches with people when I simply explain what I'm doing.  They tell me I cannot camp a whole zone and everything is fair game.<br><br>I've accepted that I have no fair claim on anything in that zone so I try to just turn the other cheek when it happens.  Half the time I wonder if they are telling me the truth about &quot;just passing by&quot;.  If I notice that someone else is &quot;camping&quot; the cycles here, I do not interfere out of courtesy, but I wonder if I have to seeing as other people don't seem to give a flying f uck about me.<br><br>Anyway, do I have any right to get mad at anyone for killing the mob that I worked for two or more hours to get to spawn? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/upidany.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Pidany</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 38<br> <font color=#E9D756>(3/22/02 11:51:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3184.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Camps and KSing and more</span><hr size=1> It's nice to see how others interpret camps and the handling of them. For the most part since starting on EMarr there have been many occasions where people are polite and respectful to each other and ofetn share camps with clear understanding. If no one tells you how they work as a noob you will find a select few that just need the explaination put in plain terms and are fine with it. Big learning process trying to figure out what's a camp and what isn't. Ks'ing should only take one good OOC exchange and you never do it again (hopefully).<br>As for the cycled spawns I would have to say that most people will have no idea that you are intentionally running them. If you do a zone wide shout maybe, but most are actually there to gain exp or to play with friends. This is especially true in TT. We had a group there just sitting on the side wall killing some named mobs playing together as a friendly weekly thing. If you are triggering them and we happen to be pulling there is no real way for us to know that is what you are doing. It is very difficult to claim all the spawns just because you say you are doing that. Really that is the main reason people hunt in TT to begin with. I am sorry you feel slighted by this but not everyone is out to intentinally piss you off, sometimes it just happens that way.<br>Bug hug for you and I am sincere in this. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uneebbo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Neebbo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 50<br> <font color=#E9D756>(3/22/02 12:22:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3184.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Camps and KSing and more</span><hr size=1>   Zone wide cycles are just too widespread in my opinion to call camp on. However, people waiting with a tracker to jump all over your spawned mob are very much camp stealers. Realistically, people do just pass through and see a mob on track and get there and kill it, often not even knowing what it drops. Given the way the spawning was designed, either you accept that other people get a shot at these mobs you worked to spawn too, or you have groups ready to engage at each spawn area. That places them basically in the South Ro AC type of situation, the difference being that only one mob is valued in all the SRO killing.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/bemarr.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=yalladar>Yalladar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#E9D756>(3/22/02 1:16:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3184.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Camps and KSing and more</span><hr size=1> [/quote] I am sorry you feel slighted by this but not everyone is out to intentinally piss you off, sometimes it just happens that way.<br>Bug hug for you and I am sincere in this. [/quote]<br><br>I do not feel like people are out to piss me off.  If I did, I would have major psychological issues.  I know the majority of people just saw this named guy and decided to kill him.  it sounds innocent enough to me.  But when I calmly explain to someone what I've been doing and they tell me to f uck off, I admit I get a little upset by this.  I've had many polite exchanges about this.  I've said something like &quot;Hi, were you planning to run the cycles?&quot;, they usually say something to me like &quot;Huh?&quot;.  This leads me to believe that they did not know that the spawn they just killed was triggered.  So right away, I'm not upset because it sounds like they just didn't know.<br><br>Usually after explaining what I am trying to do, most are pleasant with me and say they were just passing through or something like that.  I tell them no problem.  But the ones that tell me sh-it like &quot;you cannot camp a whole zone&quot; or &quot;I saw him first&quot; just represents to me that they really could care less about what I've been trying to do.  I know it's not a &quot;camp&quot; technically, but that doesn't mean people should treat me like I don't know what I'm talking about.  Most of the time, I just swallow my anger and tell them to forget it because I know longer want to deal with them.  Then I leave out of frustration.  I try my best to not let the person know that I'm angry at them because that usually escalates the matter further than it really needs to go.  I usually politely excuse myself and leave.<br><br>I've accepted that this kind of thing happens in this type of a setting and that it's really just a game, nothing to argue extensively over, IMO. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showMessageRange?topicID=3184.topic&start=21&stop=21>2</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showPrevMessage?topicID=3184.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showNextMessage?topicID=3184.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3184.topic&index=20><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/gfx/addReply1.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.emailToFriend?topicID=3184.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.threadControl?topicID=3184.topic><img src=http